message.content: A 60-year-old Caucasian male with a family history of colon cancer presents with abdominal pain, rectal bleeding, and changes in bowel habits.
A 60-year-old Caucasian male with a history of smoking and family history of colon cancer presents with abdominal pain, rectal bleeding, and changes in bowel habits.

A 65-year-old Caucasian male with a history of hypertension and hyperlipidemia presents with complaints of abdominal pain, rectal bleeding, and changes in bowel habits, ultimately diagnosed with colon cancer.
A 65-year-old male, with a history of smoking and family history of colon cancer, presents with abdominal pain, weight loss, and change in bowel habits. Colorectal cancer screening is recommended.
